General views during the 94th Comrades Marathon on June 09, 2019 in Durban, South Africa JOHANNESBURG - The 95th edition of the Comrades Marathon will go ahead despite the coronavirus outbreak. The Comrades Association's Board convened an urgent meeting on Monday evening in light of the outbreak. READ: PSL suspends all mid-week, weekend games With nearly three months to go to this year's edition, the board believes it would be premature to postpone the event. It will review the situation by the 17th of April. CMA Chairperson, Cheryl Winn urged all Comrades runners to continue with their training preparations for the 95th edition of the Marathon. The pandemic has led to the postponement or cancellation of several sporting events and mass gatherings globally. South Africa's Premier Soccer League was on Monday also officially suspended. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.